To demonstrate the presented model we consider a practical system resembling Nd3+:YAG SPL. The main absorption line of Nd3+:YAG is at 808 nm30, hence we assume that our sensitized Nd3+:YAG has an absorption band between 280 nm to 808 nm with absorption constant αa. Consequently, the Stokes’ shift of the sensitized Nd3+:YAG lasing at λL = 1064 nm26, 30–32 is 256 nm, which is approximately x1.5 times larger than the minimally thermodynamically allowed value at non-concentrated solar illumination at room temperature. The rest of parameters are ηp~100%, the loss constant at lasing wavelength αL=3⋅10−3cm−1\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
